1 unit Apple
2 teaspoon Dijon Mustard
1 unit Cranberry Jam
4 slice Sourdough Bread
½ cup Cheddar Cheese
¼ cup Monterey Jack Cheese
2 teaspoon Cooking Oil

• Wash and dry produce.

• Halve, core, and thinly slice half the apple (all for 4 servings).

• In a small bowl, stir together Dijon and jam.

• Lay bread out on a clean work surface. Spread half the bread slices with
cranberry-Dijon jam. Layer with cheddar and as many apple slices as
you like. Top with Monterey Jack and remaining bread slices.

• Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over
medium heat. Add sandwiches. Cook until bread is golden brown
and cheese melts, 3-4 minutes per side. TIP: You may need to work in
batches, adding another drizzle of oil for each batch.

• Cut grilled cheese sandos in half on a diagonal and divide between
plates. Serve with any remaining apple slices.